description: This paper proposes a machine learning-based framework to detect spam in IoT devices. Five models are evaluated on the REFIT Smart Home dataset, each generating a spam score based on input features to assess device trust. Results show the proposed method improves IoT security over existing techniques.

This project presents a two-stage machine learning-based defense system designed to detect and prevent IoT botnet attacks effectively. With the exponential rise of connected IoT devices, botnet attacks pose a serious security threatthis project aims to mitigate those risks through an intelligent and automated framework.

Python-based machine learning framework to forecast short-term stock price direction and dynamically construct a long-short portfolio optimized for maximum risk-adjusted returns. The project covers data cleaning, feature engineering, model evaluation, backtesting, and comprehensive risk-return analysis.

brpc is an Industrial-grade RPC framework using C++ Language, which is often used in high performance system such as Search, Storage, Machine learning, Advertisement, Recommendation etc. "brpc" means "better RPC".
